Denial of trial on mitigating circumstances for defendant, who pleaded guilty to second degree murder of peace officer with use of firearm and was subject to life imprisonment without possibility of parole, did not violate equal protection or due process, even though defendants who plead guilty to second degree murder with prior murder may be entitled to weighing process; crimes had distinct elements, and rational basis existed to treat different second degree murders differently. People v. Rhodes (App. 1 Dist. 2005) 24 Cal.Rptr.3d 834, 126 Cal.App.4th 1374 , review denied , habeas corpus denied 2010 WL 291781 .
